[
    {
        "content": "<p>I occasionally wish that when navigating over the <code>using</code> from <code>simpa [foo] using bar</code> that Lean would show the goal state after the simp but before attempting to finish off applying <code>bar</code>. Is this sensical to want, and if so how feasible does implementing it sound?</p>",
        "id": 538101878,
        "sender_full_name": "Julian Berman",
        "timestamp": 1757275224
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this does not sound too hard to implement</p>",
        "id": 538102276,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757275674
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That doesn't quite make sense, because the <code>simp</code> can act on both the goal and on <code>bar</code>.</p>",
        "id": 538104882,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1757278433
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess stepping back one step then, it'd be nice to somewhere see all three things (what happened to the goal, what happened to <code>bar</code>, and how close the two were to each other). Right now converting a multiline <code>have + simp</code> into <code>simpa using</code> is shorter but loses the ability to see what happens in between.</p>",
        "id": 538106107,
        "sender_full_name": "Julian Berman",
        "timestamp": 1757279970
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>hold on, which state do you want to show here?</p>",
        "id": 538106181,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757280031
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's a point where it simplifies both to the same  state, right?</p>",
        "id": 538106190,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1757280044
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or is the algorithm not \"apply simp lemmas to the goal and the <code>using</code> term until <code>exact</code> solves the former with the latter\"?</p>",
        "id": 538106214,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1757280067
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The algorithm is roughly</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">focus</span>\n<span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">disch</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">disch</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"n\">options</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">only?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">thms</span><span class=\"bp\">...</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">first</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dbg_trace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"try 'simp' instead of 'simpa'\"</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">term</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">?_</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rotate_right</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">disch</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">disch</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"n\">options</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">only?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">thms</span><span class=\"bp\">...</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">first</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dbg_trace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"try 'simp at h' instead of 'simpa'\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">done</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>i.e.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>simplify the main goal using all of the specified options. If this closes the goal and <code>linter.unnecessarySimpa</code> is enabled, print a warning</li>\n<li>elaborate the provided term with no expected type but postponing allowed</li>\n<li>create a new goal with the same type and tag</li>\n<li>introduce <code>h</code> as a new local declaration</li>\n<li>simplify <code>h</code> using all of the specified options. If this closed the goal and <code>linter.unnecessarySimpa</code> is enabled, print a warning</li>\n<li>rename <code>h</code> to <code>h✝</code> (a hygienic identifier with name <code>h</code>)</li>\n<li>elaborate <code>mkIdent `h</code> with the expected type being the goal type</li>\n<li>try to synthesize all synthetic metavariables</li>\n<li>check that the elaborated expression has the correct type while allowing assignments of synthetic opaque metavariables</li>\n<li>print an error if there are unassigned metavariables</li>\n<li>try closing the goal with the elaborated expression</li>\n<li>assign the original goal with the copied goal</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 538107767,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1757282074
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so complicated</p>",
        "id": 538107869,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757282220
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Lean.Elab.Tactic.Simpa.evalSimpa#doc\">docs#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Simpa.evalSimpa</a></p>",
        "id": 538107892,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757282256
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Now I'm reminded this is in core), but for some simple example without yet understanding precisely which step in that sequence it'd go at, what I was trying to say was comparing the <code>simpa</code> version to a 2-line version:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- Somewhere on this line, show me:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">--</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- f : Nat → Nat</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- n : Nat</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- this : f n = n + 1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- ⊢ f n = n + 1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simpa</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">add_zero</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">add_comm</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">using</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">add_zero</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">add_comm</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 538108965,
        "sender_full_name": "Julian Berman",
        "timestamp": 1757283609
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, the key difference here is that <code>hf n</code> doesn't need any simplification.</p>\n<p>My favorite way to use <code>simpa</code> is when I can build a slightly more complicated term (e.g., with <code>congr()</code>) to supply with <code>using</code> which, after simplifying it and the goal, matches somewhere.</p>",
        "id": 538204402,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1757332552
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/10309\">lean4#10309</a> is an experiment adding intermediate tactic info in the range <code>simpa ... using</code>, so all the positions in this range in <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"321696\">@Julian Berman</span>'s example show</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span>\n<span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span>\n<span class=\"n\">hf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(\"in the range\" means that you see this state if your cursor is after <code>s</code> and before the term after <code>using</code>).</p>\n<p>It doesn't show simplifications for the provided <code>using</code> term.</p>",
        "id": 538272329,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1757349008
    },
